# Topic 19: Notebook Workflows ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Concept

Notebook Workflows allow one notebook to execute another, enabling modular ETL pipelines.

---

## Theory

Methods:

* `%run` → Imports another notebook (same session).
* `dbutils.notebook.run()` → Executes another notebook (new session) and returns a value.

> **Use `%run` for shared code and `dbutils.notebook.run()` for orchestration.**

---

## Architecture

```text
Main Notebook
      │
      ▼
Notebook A
      │
      ▼
Notebook B
      │
      ▼
Notebook C
```

---

## Syntax

### Import another notebook

```python
%run /Shared/CommonFunctions
```

### Execute another notebook

```python
result = dbutils.notebook.run(
    "/Shared/LoadSales",
    300,
    {"date":"2026-06-27"}
)
```

---

