# ⭐ Interview Cheat Sheet

| Topic                    | One-line Answer                                                 |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Widgets                  | Pass runtime parameters to notebooks.                           |
| Markdown                 | Documents notebook logic for readability.                       |
| `%run`                   | Imports another notebook into the same session.                 |
| `dbutils.notebook.run()` | Executes another notebook in a new session and returns a value. |

---

## 🔥 Common Interview Question

**Q:** What is the difference between `%run` and `dbutils.notebook.run()`?

| `%run`               | `dbutils.notebook.run()`        |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Same session         | New session                     |
| Imports notebook     | Executes notebook               |
| Used for shared code | Used for workflow orchestration |
| No return value      | Returns a string value          |
| Faster               | Slightly slower                 |

**Memorize this table.** It's one of the most frequently asked Databricks interview questions.

